Hey.

270
00:18:31,617 --> 00:18:34,950
Don't worry. With this money
I'll buy you a ton of marbles.

271
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:36,333
For real?

272
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,541
You're dreaming, dude.

273
00:18:39,958 --> 00:18:40,958
Come on, come on.

274
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,541
It will be fine.

275
00:19:07,484 --> 00:19:10,125
Train to Dax,
is about to depart.

276
00:19:10,292 --> 00:19:13,250
Please move away from
the edge of the track.

277
00:19:14,208 --> 00:19:15,666
There is no room left.

278
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,541
The children...
Let the kids go first.

279
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,291
It's full.

280
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:23,374
Excuse me.

281
00:19:24,208 --> 00:19:25,416
Sorry. Thank you.

282
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:27,833
Sorry.

283
00:19:30,797 --> 00:19:31,672
Sorry.

284
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:33,833
Excuse me.

285
00:19:40,363 --> 00:19:41,529
Excuse me, can we sit here?

286
00:19:41,554 --> 00:19:42,429
Of course.

287
00:19:42,454 --> 00:19:43,343
Thank you.

288
00:19:43,398 --> 00:19:44,398
Excuse me.

289
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:51,999
- Do you think they are fleeing like us?
- How would I know?

290
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:53,833
I dunno.

291
00:19:59,292 --> 00:20:00,833
We're going to Dax.

292
00:20:01,042 --> 00:20:02,583
And then to the south.

293
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:23,124
It had started. We had left.

294
00:20:23,809 --> 00:20:25,975
Our first night without parents.

295
00:20:26,958 --> 00:20:28,916
What exactly were we fleeing from?

296
00:20:40,917 --> 00:20:43,875
Jo. Jo, wake up.
We have a problem.

297
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:50,458
Honey, hurry up.

298
00:20:50,625 --> 00:20:52,291
What is happening ?

299
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,533
Where is everyone going?

300
00:20:57,658 --> 00:21:01,142
I don't know. There are many
jumping out before stopping.

301
00:21:17,875 --> 00:21:18,708
Come.

302
00:21:25,876 --> 00:21:26,876
Paper...

303
00:21:29,958 --> 00:21:30,833
Psst.

304
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,916
We have no papers Father.

305
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:43,250
If you radiate fear, they
will notice. So don't be afraid.

306
00:21:43,665 --> 00:21:44,665
Thank you.

307
00:21:51,513 --> 00:21:52,755
Identification card!

308
00:21:59,583 --> 00:22:00,416
Eat that.

309
00:22:03,606 --> 00:22:04,567
Follow us.

310
00:22:05,875 --> 00:22:07,458
Follow us.
Stay calm.

311
00:22:07,625 --> 00:22:08,750
Your papers.

312
00:22:13,542 --> 00:22:14,458
Papers.

313
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:19,416
I don't understand German.

314
00:22:27,788 --> 00:22:28,788
Fritz!

315
00:22:29,109 --> 00:22:30,382
She's for you.

316
00:22:30,921 --> 00:22:32,882
Is there a problem, sir?"

317
00:22:36,015 --> 00:22:38,265
- So, grandma, come with me.
- Papers?

318
00:22:42,417 --> 00:22:43,250
Go.

319
00:22:45,958 --> 00:22:46,921
Thank you.

320
00:22:46,992 --> 00:22:48,672
Identification card! Now!

321
00:22:48,917 --> 00:22:50,000
Papers.

322
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:01,542
Yes,

323
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:04,108
I have lost a lot of
weight, but it is me.

324
00:23:12,101 --> 00:23:13,101
Faster!

325
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:18,686
"Gott mit uns."

326
00:23:19,348 --> 00:23:20,874
God is with you.

327
00:23:22,417 --> 00:23:23,333
That is beautiful.

328
00:23:23,542 --> 00:23:25,167
With us all, by the way.

329
00:23:25,192 --> 00:23:26,374
Hey, kids?

330
00:23:28,765 --> 00:23:30,765
The children belong to me.

331
00:23:43,741 --> 00:23:45,241
Good. Thank you.

332
00:23:46,077 --> 00:23:47,077
Paper?

333
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:49,236
Paper?

334
00:23:49,292 --> 00:23:51,375
We're going, we're going.

335
00:23:55,208 --> 00:23:56,632
You come with us.

336
00:23:57,125 --> 00:23:59,507
- There must be a mistake!
- You have to come.

337
00:23:59,671 --> 00:24:02,546
Let me go.
No, I do not want to follow you.

338
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,791
What are they doing
with that grandmother?

339
00:24:04,944 --> 00:24:09,358
Nothing for you to concern yourself with.
Quick or we'll miss the bus.

340
00:24:10,324 --> 00:24:12,032
A moment please.

341
00:24:17,022 --> 00:24:19,062
Thank you Father
that you lied for us.

342
00:24:19,179 --> 00:24:23,290
I didn't lie. All children
in the world belong to me.

343
00:24:23,383 --> 00:24:25,241
That's all. Go now.

344
00:24:25,296 --> 00:24:26,365
Hurry up.
Hey, psst.

345
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:29,772
Don't trust anyone, okay?

346
00:24:29,856 --> 00:24:31,405
And smile a little.

347
00:24:31,463 --> 00:24:33,515
You don't get apples every day.

348
00:24:34,083 --> 00:24:35,166
Good luck.

349
00:24:58,125 --> 00:24:59,694
Come on. Let's go.

350
00:25:03,542 --> 00:25:05,116
We're following them.

351
00:25:09,145 --> 00:25:12,108
There's still a spot in the back.
Follow me.

352
00:25:13,156 --> 00:25:14,256
Come on, come on.

353
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,507
Did you see it? There are
many people in that restaurant.

354
00:25:28,474 --> 00:25:31,599
Did you see ? They are
also looking for the ferryman.

355
00:25:33,133 --> 00:25:35,616
If we stay here we're
sure to get caught.

356
00:25:38,233 --> 00:25:40,458
Hey, you looking for a ferryman?

357
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:43,444
No, I'm fine.

358
00:25:44,350 --> 00:25:47,366
The ferryman comes here at
eight o'clock to pick up people.

359
00:25:47,792 --> 00:25:50,417
His name is Bronchet.
He asks 10,000 francs per person.

360
00:25:50,583 --> 00:25:51,499
20000 francs!

361
00:25:51,708 --> 00:25:52,708
Ergh... yes.

362
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:58,608
With me, it would be cheaper,
but you're not looking for a ferryman.

363
00:25:59,875 --> 00:26:03,194
How much would it cost?
Just for example...

364
00:26:04,098 --> 00:26:09,203
Let's say...
1000 per person, without negotiation.

365
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:11,289
And with negotiations?

366
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:13,155
See you later, Parisians.

367
00:26:13,218 --> 00:26:14,398
We can pay.

368
00:26:14,468 --> 00:26:16,429
Well, what do you know?

369
00:26:16,917 --> 00:26:20,819
Good. You give me half now
and the rest on arrival.

370
00:26:32,436 --> 00:26:33,693
Agreement concluded.

371
00:26:34,807 --> 00:26:35,733
Good.

372
00:26:36,167 --> 00:26:40,417
I will continue with my delivery
round first, then I'll poke a trout...

373
00:26:40,921 --> 00:26:44,725
and we'll meet on that corner
of the street when night falls.

374
00:26:45,187 --> 00:26:47,280
We're not leaving now?
Oh no.

375
00:26:47,546 --> 00:26:50,132
That's too dangerous.
Okay, see you later!

376
00:26:51,022 --> 00:26:54,000
- My name is Raymond.
- Hi, Raymond. Me, it's Jo.

377
00:26:55,875 --> 00:26:57,257
That man was nice, isn't he?

378
00:26:57,282 --> 00:26:59,771
- "Hey Raymond, I'm Jo."
- That will cost us a thousand marbles!

379
00:26:59,950 --> 00:27:02,658
You're joking?
We just saved 18,000.

380
00:27:16,542 --> 00:27:18,500
We're better off here
than in Clignancourt, huh?

381
00:27:18,667 --> 00:27:20,417
Yes, we certainly are.

382
00:27:20,987 --> 00:27:22,653
- I'm going to pee.
- Yes.

383
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:27,239
Come on.

384
00:27:27,264 --> 00:27:29,375
Come on little one. Come!

385
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:34,437
Watch out. The Germans!

386
00:27:43,167 --> 00:27:45,083
- I got you.
- Shit.

387
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:49,453
Your cock is circumcised, isn't it, 'little boy'.

388
00:27:49,478 --> 00:27:52,016
- "Jew, you are."
- You're stupid.

389
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:53,968
You pissed on it.

390
00:27:54,096 --> 00:27:56,221
Come on, come on.

391
00:27:56,438 --> 00:27:58,438
No, no you're not wiping it on me.

392
00:28:13,167 --> 00:28:15,750
It's almost dark.
What the hell is he doing?

393
00:28:15,854 --> 00:28:17,520
There's no one here anymore.

394
00:28:17,750 --> 00:28:20,320
He went to poke a trout,
didn't you hear that?

395
00:28:20,792 --> 00:28:22,875
And what does that mean?

396
00:28:23,583 --> 00:28:25,249
It sounds disgusting.

397
00:28:25,417 --> 00:28:27,062
I have no idea.

398
00:28:41,125 --> 00:28:44,695
We got ourselves conned by Raymond.
Papa had warned us.

399
00:28:51,083 --> 00:28:52,624
Quick!

400
00:28:55,708 --> 00:28:56,772
Don't move.

401
00:28:59,226 --> 00:29:00,250
Get down.

402
00:29:12,667 --> 00:29:13,583
Look...

403
00:29:13,792 --> 00:29:16,458
They're searching everywhere.
We'll never get out of here.

404
00:29:18,311 --> 00:29:21,413
- I want to see Papa and Maman.
- Calm down.

405
00:29:22,208 --> 00:29:25,541
This is not the time to cry.
We'll wait a little longer.

406
00:29:30,458 --> 00:29:31,291
Damn it.

407
00:29:31,487 --> 00:29:33,903
Hey Parisians! Are you OK?

408
00:29:36,708 --> 00:29:37,890
Come with me.

409
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:42,666
Go.

410
00:29:45,292 --> 00:29:46,375
Come on, little one.

411
00:29:56,875 --> 00:29:57,750
Come on!

412
00:29:58,875 --> 00:29:59,916
Be careful.

413
00:30:06,292 --> 00:30:07,125
Stand up.

414
00:30:08,667 --> 00:30:10,250
Hey! Psst. This way.

415
00:30:19,601 --> 00:30:21,390
Father Bronchet's been caught.

416
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:24,583
It had to happen eventually.

417
00:30:24,833 --> 00:30:26,656
He transfers twelve at a time.

418
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:28,703
They make too much noise.

419
00:30:29,385 --> 00:30:32,132
Please.
Please.

420
00:30:32,312 --> 00:30:33,708
We're lost.

421
00:30:33,917 --> 00:30:35,960
Come. Come.

422
00:30:36,293 --> 00:30:37,334
Come down!

423
00:30:38,364 --> 00:30:40,234
I'm with my wife and my mother.

424
00:30:40,625 --> 00:30:43,562
Our ferryman has abandoned us.
I beg you to help us.

425
00:30:48,518 --> 00:30:49,908
It's 1000 per head.

426
00:30:50,065 --> 00:30:53,197
The little one is free, but...
I don't want to hear him. Good?

427
00:30:53,252 --> 00:30:55,166
Very good.
Thank you sir.

428
00:30:55,348 --> 00:30:56,181
"Sir"?

429
00:30:58,250 --> 00:30:59,375
He's funny...

430
00:31:03,424 --> 00:31:06,104
Come on, it's okay. Pass it over.

431
00:31:06,708 --> 00:31:07,541
Go.

432
00:31:18,121 --> 00:31:19,893
Do you see that barn over there?

433
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:23,487
It's open. The farmer is aware.

434
00:31:23,955 --> 00:31:26,314
Go in. You can sleep on the straw.

435
00:31:26,433 --> 00:31:28,433
Thank you.
Thank you.

436
00:31:30,208 --> 00:31:32,433
Hey, are we in the free zone there?

437
00:31:32,458 --> 00:31:36,354
"In the free zone"?
You've been there for 10 minutes.

438
00:31:37,417 --> 00:31:40,675
- Is that all? Was it that easy?
- Are you disappointed?

439
00:31:42,283 --> 00:31:45,026
I told you.
With me, no danger, and no Germans.

440
00:32:00,417 --> 00:32:03,862
In the free zone...
Free from what exactly?

441
00:32:05,308 --> 00:32:06,974
Are we free to be Jews?

442
00:32:07,917 --> 00:32:10,159
We're free to sleep, dummy.

443
00:32:10,583 --> 00:32:14,374
Twenty kilometers on foot,
wear out, wear out...

444
00:32:14,542 --> 00:32:18,375
Twenty kilometers on foot,
it wears out your soles.

445
00:32:19,700 --> 00:32:23,200
Twenty one kilometers on foot,
wear out, wear out...

446
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:27,166
Twenty one kilometers on foot,
it wears out your soles.

447
00:32:27,333 --> 00:32:31,291
Twenty two kilometers on foot,
wear out, wear out...

448
00:32:31,500 --> 00:32:35,166
Twenty two kilometers on foot,
it wears out your soles.

449
00:32:35,573 --> 00:32:38,125
Twenty three kilometers on foot...

450
00:32:38,292 --> 00:32:40,708
- Are you limping?
- No, it's nothing.

451
00:32:40,867 --> 00:32:42,706
- Your foot hurts.
- It's nothing!

452
00:32:42,761 --> 00:32:45,000
Show me. Sit down.

453
00:32:54,796 --> 00:32:55,853
Shit.

454
00:32:58,169 --> 00:33:00,135
You can't walk with that anymore.

455
00:33:01,417 --> 00:33:03,510
It is not worth insisting.

456
00:33:13,875 --> 00:33:15,338
Come on, come on.

457
00:33:15,583 --> 00:33:18,385
Grab your bag.
I'll take you on my back.

458
00:33:21,242 --> 00:33:22,200
Go.

459
00:33:32,708 --> 00:33:34,666
Do you know your feet stink?

460
00:33:34,833 --> 00:33:36,541
Your ass stinks.

461
00:33:37,917 --> 00:33:39,292
But thanks anyway.

462
00:33:39,458 --> 00:33:42,135
That's normal, you're
my little brother.

463
00:33:42,208 --> 00:33:45,322
I would carry you to the end
of the world, if necessary.

464
00:33:49,387 --> 00:33:51,525
Come on, get off. You're too heavy.

465
00:33:56,877 --> 00:34:00,250
- Until the end of the world, huh?
- Oh, you're getting on my nerves...

466
00:34:17,432 --> 00:34:20,205
- What? Are we lazy?
- No, it's my brother...

467
00:34:20,307 --> 00:34:22,572
- My brother is too tired to walk.
- Come on, get in!

468
00:34:22,625 --> 00:34:23,750
Go ahead, get up.

469
00:34:25,750 --> 00:34:27,439
Okay, here we go!

470
00:34:39,651 --> 00:34:41,692
- That's Adolf.
- What are you going to do with it?

471
00:34:41,807 --> 00:34:43,603
What did you think?
We'll make him bleed.

472
00:34:43,659 --> 00:34:45,127
We make black pudding from his blood.

473
00:34:45,221 --> 00:34:46,768
And then rillettes and bacon.

474
00:34:46,885 --> 00:34:48,307
And of course meat.

475
00:34:48,494 --> 00:34:49,785
Turn around, Adolf.

476
00:34:50,083 --> 00:34:51,627
That's her ass.

477
00:34:51,705 --> 00:34:54,728
You don't think that she's
going to shoot at us, huh?

478
00:34:55,666 --> 00:34:57,893
Adolf, kaputt!

479
00:35:13,208 --> 00:35:17,025
Maurice and I changed our route
to avoid highways.

480
00:35:17,266 --> 00:35:20,849
It was too good to be like
that, to travel freely...

481
00:35:21,125 --> 00:35:22,958
like we've never done before.

482
00:35:23,572 --> 00:35:26,530
We ended up forgetting that we
were running away from something.

483
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:29,166
There were no parents, no school,

484
00:35:29,333 --> 00:35:32,499
And above all, no one
to tell us what to do.

485
00:35:39,542 --> 00:35:42,533
Watch out, little one.
That's not for girls.

486
00:35:44,042 --> 00:35:46,250
We meet all sorts
of people on our journey.

487
00:35:46,458 --> 00:35:48,385
Some more fun than others...

488
00:35:49,205 --> 00:35:50,885
But everyone was afraid.

489
00:35:51,135 --> 00:35:53,000
You could see it in their eyes.

490
00:35:53,458 --> 00:35:55,603
Even though everyone
was pretending.

491
00:36:03,292 --> 00:36:04,564
Oh, look there!

492
00:36:08,042 --> 00:36:09,208
Wow.

493
00:36:14,125 --> 00:36:15,291
I can not believe my eyes.

494
00:36:16,292 --> 00:36:18,111
How blue it is!

495
00:36:21,375 --> 00:36:23,791
Look. We've finally arrived.

496
00:36:32,900 --> 00:36:34,700
Hey boy, you're losing your coat.

497
00:36:36,042 --> 00:36:37,042
Thank you sir.

498
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:51,481
Hey, I'm taking a picture!

499
00:36:52,042 --> 00:36:55,667
Come on, I don't bite.
I eat you alone...

500
00:36:56,705 --> 00:36:59,439
Come on, you take
your time. The beauty...

501
00:37:00,830 --> 00:37:03,635
Those Italians are more
relaxed than the Germans.

502
00:37:03,660 --> 00:37:06,132
Come on, let's find our parents.

503
00:37:13,792 --> 00:37:16,416
Turnips or Jerusalem artichokes?

504
00:37:23,583 --> 00:37:24,416
Jo.

505
00:37:42,375 --> 00:37:43,750
The beautiful fish!

506
00:37:47,167 --> 00:37:48,971
Hello. Are you looking for something?

507
00:37:49,268 --> 00:37:52,041
Mister Levine's hair salon, please?

508
00:37:52,208 --> 00:37:53,557
It's right there.

509
00:37:57,722 --> 00:38:00,263
Hello.
Oh, the children! Great.

510
00:38:00,288 --> 00:38:01,204
Albert!

511
00:38:02,859 --> 00:38:03,900
Albert!

512
00:38:09,234 --> 00:38:10,067
Look.

513
00:38:20,292 --> 00:38:24,057
It seems that happiness
passes faster than sadness.

514
00:38:25,958 --> 00:38:27,874
We were finally all together.

515
00:38:29,208 --> 00:38:31,124
The rest did not exist.

516
00:38:32,625 --> 00:38:34,533
He still needs his Maman and Papa.

517
00:38:34,558 --> 00:38:37,099
Especially his father to dry his hair.

518
00:38:37,792 --> 00:38:38,958
You're not cold?

519
00:38:39,112 --> 00:38:40,278
Okay darling ?

520
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:44,381
Never again do you leave me like that.
Never again. Promised.

521
00:38:45,250 --> 00:38:46,083
Never again.

522
00:38:49,992 --> 00:38:50,950
Never again.

523
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,291
I was afraid.

524
00:38:56,378 --> 00:38:57,961
We too were afraid.

525
00:38:59,083 --> 00:39:01,499
When you have children of your own,
you will understand.

526
00:39:04,625 --> 00:39:06,869
I'm so proud of you, son.

527
00:39:08,292 --> 00:39:09,583
So proud.

528
00:39:10,458 --> 00:39:13,893
I will always be there in your heart.

529
00:39:14,667 --> 00:39:15,666
Always.

530
00:39:21,792 --> 00:39:22,833
You are crazy!

531
00:39:24,250 --> 00:39:25,333
Go. Watch out.

532
00:39:25,500 --> 00:39:26,666
