00:54:56,490 --> 00:54:59,101
Okay Algerian, show us what you
have in your belly.

796
00:55:00,555 --> 00:55:01,687
Next one!

797
00:55:03,453 --> 00:55:04,508
Hey, Joffo!

798
00:55:05,099 --> 00:55:07,422
If we tell that, where do we live?

799
00:55:07,447 --> 00:55:09,867
- Rue Jean-Jaures 10.
- What about Jean-Jaures?

800
00:55:09,892 --> 00:55:12,725
Because there's always a
Jean-Jaures street and it's easy to remember.

801
00:55:12,883 --> 00:55:15,424
The rest remains as it is is:
the house, the drawing room...

802
00:55:15,677 --> 00:55:17,859
Papa is a hairdresser,
Maman plays the violin.

803
00:55:17,919 --> 00:55:19,859
Then we cannot make any mistakes.

804
00:55:20,281 --> 00:55:21,859
Come on. Come on!

805
00:55:22,403 --> 00:55:24,403
You're not too stupid, either.

806
00:55:27,198 --> 00:55:28,489
Come on, you follow.

807
00:55:31,924 --> 00:55:33,007
We accelerate!

808
00:55:37,612 --> 00:55:38,445
Come on!

809
00:55:38,939 --> 00:55:40,772
- Ouch!
- Let's practice it.

810
00:55:41,096 --> 00:55:43,336
Where do you go to school, 'little boy'?"

811
00:55:44,341 --> 00:55:46,617
Rue Jean-Jaurès.
In the same street where...

812
00:55:46,642 --> 00:55:49,351
- What is your mother's name?
- Anne Marie.

813
00:55:49,390 --> 00:55:52,094
- And your father?
- Roman.

814
00:55:52,485 --> 00:55:53,610
That's good.

815
00:55:54,322 --> 00:55:55,539
Come on, let's go.

816
00:56:07,747 --> 00:56:09,038
I miss them.

817
00:56:10,354 --> 00:56:11,625
Me too.

818
00:56:12,396 --> 00:56:14,836
It's not normal,
that we don't hear from them.

819
00:56:15,672 --> 00:56:17,617
Maybe they're
suspicious of the phone.

820
00:56:18,195 --> 00:56:19,461
I want to see them.

821
00:56:21,880 --> 00:56:24,086
- We don't know where they are.
- So what? I want to see them!

822
00:56:27,907 --> 00:56:30,198
We're accelerating a bit here.

823
00:56:34,198 --> 00:56:37,323
Guys, tell me, do you
have family in Nice?

824
00:56:38,391 --> 00:56:40,937
- No, let's go for a walk.
- Walk around?

825
00:56:41,469 --> 00:56:44,976
Are you going to the Promenade
des Anglais to see the girls?

826
00:56:45,142 --> 00:56:46,422
Yes that's it.

827
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:48,922
Don't say stupid things,
that he doesn't believe.

828
00:56:48,981 --> 00:56:51,031
You don't have to be
ashamed when you look at girls.

829
00:56:51,087 --> 00:56:55,156
In a few years they will be looking
at you too. You're good looking enough.

830
00:56:55,424 --> 00:56:56,648
Watch out!

831
00:57:00,220 --> 00:57:02,053
That's sensational, isn't it!

832
00:57:02,219 --> 00:57:03,836
Wow! Go on.

833
00:57:05,240 --> 00:57:06,961
We're gonna look at the girls!

834
00:57:07,448 --> 00:57:10,698
WE WILL WATCH THE GIRLS!
WE WILL SEE GIRLS!

835
00:57:17,953 --> 00:57:19,383
This is not the market...

836
00:57:19,408 --> 00:57:22,101
I need two minutes.
Wait for me. I will return.

837
00:57:25,008 --> 00:57:26,664
Wait here, huh?
I'm counting on you.

838
00:57:28,096 --> 00:57:29,179
Shh.

839
00:57:35,453 --> 00:57:37,469
It's not funny. Open your door.

840
00:57:37,713 --> 00:57:38,820
How do you do that?

841
00:57:38,845 --> 00:57:41,039
Don't you know how open a door?

842
00:58:04,823 --> 00:58:08,062
- Don't you get tired of doing nothing?
- No...

843
00:58:13,870 --> 00:58:16,609
He's been gone for a while.
What the hell is he doing?

844
00:58:17,252 --> 00:58:18,668
He said to wait.

845
00:58:21,929 --> 00:58:23,345
Come on, stay.

846
00:58:25,166 --> 00:58:27,461
You're waiting for me.
Above all, you do not move.

847
00:58:27,906 --> 00:58:30,961
I'll tell him we're going
to the market on foot.

848
00:59:38,830 --> 00:59:39,862
Jo.

849
00:59:41,088 --> 00:59:42,222
Are you okay?

850
00:59:43,490 --> 00:59:45,698
- Okay, okay.
- Sit up.

851
00:59:49,557 --> 00:59:51,315
You promised not to move.

852
00:59:53,476 --> 00:59:54,601
I'm sorry.

853
01:00:05,089 --> 01:00:07,761
Children! You say nothing.

854
01:00:16,657 --> 01:00:17,740
Quickly.

855
01:00:34,797 --> 01:00:36,005
Meyer, Martha.

856
01:00:37,956 --> 01:00:38,831
Hurry.

857
01:00:40,604 --> 01:00:42,284
There's one more coming.

858
01:00:43,357 --> 01:00:44,925
Dreyfuss, Louis.

859
01:00:49,779 --> 01:00:51,445
Goldman, Gabriel.

860
01:00:55,722 --> 01:00:57,276
Epstein, Doris.

861
01:01:00,540 --> 01:01:02,198
Goldman, Mordecai.

862
01:01:06,021 --> 01:01:07,753
Abel, Adele.

863
01:01:25,393 --> 01:01:26,870
Walk! Walk!

864
01:01:27,032 --> 01:01:28,370
Abou, Gabriel.

865
01:01:31,025 --> 01:01:32,440
Saul, Levin.

866
01:01:34,740 --> 01:01:36,031
It's Levine.

867
01:01:36,263 --> 01:01:37,346
It's Levine.

868
01:01:37,620 --> 01:01:39,060
Goldfarb, Michael.

869
01:01:40,059 --> 01:01:41,924
And do you see Maman and Papa?

870
01:02:22,180 --> 01:02:25,846
Usually, I begin by asking
name, first name and religion.

871
01:02:26,149 --> 01:02:27,690
But here I am lost.

872
01:02:28,599 --> 01:02:30,409
Why all these false papers?

873
01:02:31,807 --> 01:02:32,890
Are you Jewish?

874
01:02:35,607 --> 01:02:36,440
No.

875
01:02:41,883 --> 01:02:43,252
Are you not a Jew?

876
01:02:45,141 --> 01:02:45,974
No.

877
01:03:01,779 --> 01:03:02,654
So...

878
01:03:03,922 --> 01:03:05,479
You are a resistance fighter.

879
01:03:07,797 --> 01:03:08,630
No.

880
01:03:10,119 --> 01:03:12,327
We slaughter all resistance fighters.

881
01:03:12,450 --> 01:03:14,158
These are the orders.

882
01:03:18,341 --> 01:03:20,132
In German:
He is a resistance fighter.

883
01:03:26,781 --> 01:03:28,572
Unless you are Jew...

884
01:03:32,065 --> 01:03:32,898
No.

885
01:03:43,795 --> 01:03:47,010
Yes, I am a Jew.
Is that what you want to know?

886
01:03:47,307 --> 01:03:48,348
I am Jewish.

887
01:03:48,510 --> 01:03:50,218
And also a resistance fighter.

888
01:03:51,203 --> 01:03:53,911
Jew and resistance fighter.
Kill me if you want.

889
01:03:54,354 --> 01:03:57,760
It will not change anything.
You will not win the war.

890
01:03:58,198 --> 01:03:59,917
You have already lost the war.

891
01:04:00,221 --> 01:04:02,909
I am Jew and resistance fighter.

892
01:04:03,151 --> 01:04:04,284
And I shit on you!

893
01:04:04,309 --> 01:04:05,142
Stop!

894
01:04:12,588 --> 01:04:14,129
He is a resistance fighter.

895
01:04:28,071 --> 01:04:29,112
Next.

896
01:04:32,088 --> 01:04:34,088
Name, first name, religion.

897
01:04:37,633 --> 01:04:39,338
David Cohen, I'm a Jew.

898
01:04:55,971 --> 01:04:56,846
Next.

899
01:05:02,862 --> 01:05:04,752
Name, first name, religion.

900
01:05:04,777 --> 01:05:07,096
Listen, we have nothing to do with all this.

901
01:05:07,213 --> 01:05:08,963
We are from 'Moissons Nouvelles'.

902
01:05:09,252 --> 01:05:11,245
Name, first name, religion.

903
01:05:11,891 --> 01:05:13,815
Maurice Joffo, Catholic.

904
01:05:14,162 --> 01:05:18,549
We just went with Ferdinand to go shopping.
It is a mistake, sir.

905
01:05:18,779 --> 01:05:21,820
- We have nothing to do with it.
- Is that your brother ?

906
01:05:26,432 --> 01:05:28,182
Yes, it's my brother Jo.

907
01:05:33,857 --> 01:05:36,854
Jo... Like Joseph?

908
01:05:38,294 --> 01:05:39,127
Yes.

909
01:05:40,617 --> 01:05:42,221
Our mother's name is Marie.

910
01:05:48,778 --> 01:05:49,838
I see.

911
01:05:50,669 --> 01:05:52,502
So you're not a Jew?

912
01:05:53,748 --> 01:05:55,729
No, I already told you that.

913
01:05:56,306 --> 01:06:00,264
Stop! We are Algerians!
Catholic Algerians.

914
01:06:02,477 --> 01:06:03,685
We'll start again.

915
01:06:07,323 --> 01:06:08,781
Are you Jewish?

916
01:06:09,990 --> 01:06:10,823
No.

917
01:06:13,013 --> 01:06:13,846
No!

918
01:06:15,182 --> 01:06:16,140
Stop!

919
01:06:26,653 --> 01:06:27,611
Let go of me.

920
01:06:32,395 --> 01:06:34,224
To the medical examination!

921
01:06:50,924 --> 01:06:54,270
You say you are Catholic?
Yes.

922
01:06:54,344 --> 01:06:56,489
Yes, in Algeria we do
this as a precaution.

923
01:06:57,302 --> 01:06:59,036
Otherwise adhesions will occur.

924
01:06:59,442 --> 01:07:00,231
Yes sir.

925
01:07:00,383 --> 01:07:02,098
They circumcise everyone's 'zboub'.

926
01:07:02,208 --> 01:07:04,911
The Algerians, the Catholics: everyone.

927
01:07:05,727 --> 01:07:06,727
Even the Jews.

928
01:07:08,341 --> 01:07:11,278
That I do not know.
There are not many Jews there.

929
01:07:11,359 --> 01:07:13,544
I've never seen one.
On my word: that is the truth.

930
01:07:14,020 --> 01:07:14,978
Sit down.

931
01:07:17,439 --> 01:07:19,544
My name is Rosen.
Know you what that means?

932
01:07:19,731 --> 01:07:20,559
No.

933
01:07:20,741 --> 01:07:22,488
That you are pink?

934
01:07:24,156 --> 01:07:27,341
No, I am a Jew.
So you can tell me, to me,

935
01:07:28,198 --> 01:07:29,778
That you too are Jews.

936
01:07:31,734 --> 01:07:36,411
- You are Jew, but we are not.
- We are Algerian.

937
01:07:37,036 --> 01:07:39,494
That's why our 'zboub' is circumcised.

938
01:07:39,750 --> 01:07:43,247
So, Jewish or not, you
know what you have to do.

939
01:07:56,024 --> 01:07:57,315
Guard!

940
01:08:01,163 --> 01:08:03,731
It's medical, not religious.

941
01:08:03,919 --> 01:08:04,919
Please...

942
01:08:06,298 --> 01:08:07,247
Go.

943
01:08:09,680 --> 01:08:10,513
Next.

944
01:08:14,427 --> 01:08:17,468
I will always wonder why the doctor...

945
01:08:17,611 --> 01:08:19,069
had saved us.

946
01:08:19,251 --> 01:08:22,481
While every day he had
to condemn hundreds.

947
01:08:29,751 --> 01:08:32,719
On the Rue Jean-Jaures, as
I have already told you.

948
01:08:35,826 --> 01:08:37,451
The name of the school?

949
01:08:37,664 --> 01:08:39,372
The primary school in Algeria.

950
01:08:44,555 --> 01:08:46,540
The Jean-Jaurès school, I think.

951
01:08:51,258 --> 01:08:52,133
That's all ?

952
01:08:52,158 --> 01:08:54,782
Well, yes, I think.
I didn't pay attention to it.

953
01:08:54,807 --> 01:08:56,657
It's just the school, isn't it?

954
01:08:56,947 --> 01:08:58,697
Friends at school?

955
01:08:58,880 --> 01:09:01,751
Yes a lot.
Zerati is my best friend.

956
01:09:02,501 --> 01:09:04,079
He is very good with marbles.

957
01:09:04,615 --> 01:09:05,740
Zerti...

958
01:09:06,594 --> 01:09:09,665
Zerati.
He is good with marbles.

959
01:09:10,257 --> 01:09:13,508
- And what games do you play at school?
- Everything.

960
01:09:13,802 --> 01:09:17,126
Playing tag, hide and seek,
thief with redemption...

961
01:09:17,415 --> 01:09:18,610
with marbles...

962
01:09:18,635 --> 01:09:22,836
there are many:
marble pit, bowling, target shooting...

963
01:09:22,861 --> 01:09:24,821
the hole, the pyramid...

964
01:09:24,901 --> 01:09:26,567
What have I done?

965
01:09:28,110 --> 01:09:29,969
Listen to me, little one...

966
01:09:31,305 --> 01:09:33,876
I know when someone
is not telling the truth.

967
01:09:34,469 --> 01:09:35,672
And you lie.

968
01:09:36,041 --> 01:09:37,860
And your baptism?

969
01:09:38,758 --> 01:09:40,063
Where was it?

970
01:09:41,961 --> 01:09:44,001
At the great church of Algiers, surely?

971
01:09:44,313 --> 01:09:47,032
No. Here in Nice, at the Buffa.

972
01:09:47,924 --> 01:09:50,715
Mama wanted to have the family there.
That's why she preferred it here.

973
01:09:51,559 --> 01:09:54,836
Very good.
That should be easy to verify.

974
01:09:55,458 --> 01:09:57,688
A pass for 48 hours!

975
01:09:59,677 --> 01:10:02,969
You have two days to get your
baptismal certificates.

976
01:10:03,364 --> 01:10:05,555
If you're not back within 48 hours...

977
01:10:07,107 --> 01:10:09,954
I send your little brother
on the next train.

978
01:10:12,104 --> 01:10:13,395
Do you understand?

979
01:10:15,151 --> 01:10:17,016
I didn't know what to say.

980
01:10:17,201 --> 01:10:19,451
I don't know of any
churches in Algiers.

981
01:10:21,107 --> 01:10:24,454
If it turns out you can't
make it, then don't come back.

982
01:10:25,424 --> 01:10:27,840
One alive is better
than two dead, I think.

983
01:10:28,016 --> 01:10:31,485
Do not say that.
I will return with false papers.

984
01:10:32,071 --> 01:10:33,862
It's mission impossible.

985
01:10:35,904 --> 01:10:37,279
Save yourself.

986
01:10:37,385 --> 01:10:39,010
Shut up.
I will be back.

987
01:10:39,563 --> 01:10:42,540
- Jo. Something wrong?
- I am tired.

988
01:10:42,782 --> 01:10:46,672
It has been going on for a week.
I'm fed up with this bullshit.

989
01:10:46,719 --> 01:10:49,665
- I want it to stop.
- Listen to me.

990
01:10:50,672 --> 01:10:54,344
- As long as there's hope we hold on.
- Hang on, Jo.

991
01:11:04,025 --> 01:11:05,110
Maurice Joffo!

992
01:11:09,532 --> 01:11:10,735
Listen to me.

993
01:11:11,619 --> 01:11:14,160
I will return. Do you hear me?

994
01:11:15,407 --> 01:11:17,240
I'm coming back for you. Promise.

995
01:12:14,289 --> 01:12:15,955
Maman...
No, leave me alone!

996
01:12:16,048 --> 01:12:16,923
Maman.

997
01:12:17,795 --> 01:12:19,378
Leave me alone!
Maman !

998
01:12:27,476 --> 01:12:28,767
Papa...

999
01:12:33,245 --> 01:12:34,078
Jo.

1000
01:12:35,826 --> 01:12:38,251
Jo.
Papa ?

1001
01:12:38,529 --> 01:12:40,672
No, not really, Joseph.

1002
01:12:41,466 --> 01:12:44,055
Papa, I didn't say anything.

1003
01:12:44,922 --> 01:12:47,297
Do not say anything. You have
been delirious, but you are saved.

1004
01:12:47,747 --> 01:12:49,705
Sulfonamides have been effective.

1005
01:12:51,274 --> 01:12:52,524
Dr. Rozen?

1006
01:12:52,784 --> 01:12:53,950
You are lucky.

1007
01:12:54,282 --> 01:12:55,852
Meningitis is often fatal.

1008
01:12:55,965 --> 01:12:58,001
And my brother? Maurice?

1009
01:12:58,518 --> 01:13:01,524
- How many days have I been here?
- Two, three days.

1010
01:13:01,895 --> 01:13:04,103
You are cured,
that is the most important.

1011
01:13:05,001 --> 01:13:06,681
Yes. That's how it is.

1012
01:13:07,344 --> 01:13:09,599
That way I can board
the train in good health.

1013
01:13:13,368 --> 01:13:14,844
Listen to me carefully.

1014
01:13:15,701 --> 01:13:17,126
I'm the one who's going.

1015
01:13:18,391 --> 01:13:21,180
I'm going to get on the
train with everyone else later.

1016
01:13:21,634 --> 01:13:23,219
It's better that way.

1017
01:13:26,063 --> 01:13:27,229
You know, Joseph,

1018
01:13:28,032 --> 01:13:31,024
Sometimes we do things in life,
which we are not always proud of.

1019
01:13:32,188 --> 01:13:33,063
Here.

1020
01:13:34,454 --> 01:13:37,641
You held her tight in your fist, like that...
So...

1021
01:13:38,131 --> 01:13:40,951
Throughout your delirium.
You were attached to it.

1022
01:13:42,088 --> 01:13:44,088
That's all I have left from before.

1023
01:13:45,434 --> 01:13:46,944
If you keep fighting...

1024
01:13:47,788 --> 01:13:50,287
then keep your life in
your fist like this one.

1025
01:13:51,029 --> 01:13:52,615
Then you'll be fine.

1026
01:13:53,349 --> 01:13:54,974
What's the use of living?

1027
01:13:55,135 --> 01:13:57,218
It's a matter of chance.

1028
01:13:57,916 --> 01:13:58,957
It's stupid.

1029
01:13:58,982 --> 01:13:59,778
Stupid.

1030
01:13:59,802 --> 01:14:00,635
Stu...

1031
01:14:03,102 --> 01:14:04,186
Joseph...

1032
01:14:05,317 --> 01:14:07,650
Death did not want you twice.

1033
01:14:08,805 --> 01:14:11,451
That means you have a
good reason to live.

1034
01:14:14,057 --> 01:14:16,623
Do something with your
life, Joseph. Be proud of it.

1035
01:14:18,051 --> 01:14:19,873
Come on, you owe me that.

1036
01:14:31,841 --> 01:14:32,998
Goodbye, Joseph.

1037
01:14:36,270 --> 01:14:37,561
These are fakes.

1038
01:14:38,852 --> 01:14:40,459
Not at all, I assure you.

1039
01:14:41,287 --> 01:14:44,553
The Archbishop can testify that
these are authentic certificates.

1040
01:14:45,998 --> 01:14:47,483
I do not believe you.

1041
01:14:47,508 --> 01:14:48,424
Why ?

1042
01:14:51,069 --> 01:14:53,756
I recognize the truth when I see her.

1043
01:14:54,622 --> 01:14:57,366
And when I look at you...
Do you know what I see then?

1044
01:14:59,596 --> 01:15:02,897
The certificates of the priest
from Buffa, I gave to the Krauts.

1045
01:15:03,024 --> 01:15:04,928
I alerted Subinagui too.

1046
01:15:06,073 --> 01:15:07,781
He's coming for us.

1047
01:15:09,869 --> 01:15:12,225
And... Papa and Maman?

1048
01:15:20,659 --> 01:15:22,034
The salon is closed.

1049
01:15:26,322 --> 01:15:27,738
It does not matter.

1050
01:15:27,953 --> 01:15:30,639
We'll get out of here and
we'll find them one day.

1051
01:15:31,927 --> 01:15:34,201
Why do you bother about them?

1052
01:15:34,471 --> 01:15:35,721
They are Jewish.

1053
01:15:36,182 --> 01:15:39,116
- I put my hand in the fire.
- It's obsession.

1054
01:15:39,661 --> 01:15:42,129
But that doesn't change anything.
They lie.

1055
01:15:42,648 --> 01:15:45,551
And you too.
The Archbishop

1056
01:15:46,386 --> 01:15:50,198
The Archbishop does not want two
children judged on mere assumptions.

1057
01:15:50,914 --> 01:15:52,667
He will inform Rome.

1058
01:15:53,268 --> 01:15:55,965
You don't want it do you?
Have a pontificate against you?

1059
01:15:57,785 --> 01:15:59,225
Certainly not now.

1060
01:15:59,566 --> 01:16:00,824
We shall see.

1061
01:16:02,204 --> 01:16:03,162
Understood!

1062
01:16:04,756 --> 01:16:09,006
Hey brothers! Go get
me tomatoes from the garden.

1063
01:16:12,474 --> 01:16:15,099
I don't understand
why they won't let us go.

1064
01:16:20,075 --> 01:16:20,908
Come.

1065
01:16:24,820 --> 01:16:26,820
You see that vegetable garden?

1066
01:16:28,141 --> 01:16:30,605
It's very easy to escape from there.

1067
01:16:33,258 --> 01:16:34,746
There's more to that.

1068
01:16:36,698 --> 01:16:37,698
Here, there?

1069
01:16:38,032 --> 01:16:39,323
Really, very easy.

1070
01:17:02,854 --> 01:17:05,012
Maurice... look.

1071
01:17:10,607 --> 01:17:13,230
You vouch for their
innocence, don't you?

1072
01:17:16,782 --> 01:17:18,699
Did you see ?
Yes.

1073
01:17:19,271 --> 01:17:20,229
Let's go ?

1074
01:17:22,365 --> 01:17:23,906
We're going, on three.

1075
01:17:24,721 --> 01:17:25,721
One...

1076
01:17:27,716 --> 01:17:28,549
Two...

1077
01:17:31,422 --> 01:17:32,713
Three, go.

1078
01:17:33,595 --> 01:17:34,886
Watch out!

1079
01:17:35,823 --> 01:17:37,051
There's a soldier.

1080
01:17:38,367 --> 01:17:39,283
It's a trap.

1081
01:18:01,736 --> 01:18:04,319
Thank you, Father.
You saved our lives.

1082
01:18:06,102 --> 01:18:07,727
Mr. Subinagui!

1083
01:18:09,508 --> 01:18:11,105
Hello, children.

1084
01:18:11,650 --> 01:18:13,676
Thank you, Father.
You were brave.

1085
01:18:13,747 --> 01:18:15,913
I only did my duty.

1086
01:18:16,020 --> 01:18:17,754
Go in peace, my children.

1087
01:18:17,825 --> 01:18:19,863
Come on. We must not hang around here.

1088
01:18:23,309 --> 01:18:24,142
Jo.

1089
01:18:26,182 --> 01:18:27,348
Farewell, Father.

1090
01:18:28,950 --> 01:18:30,865
Go. Go.

1091
01:18:52,482 --> 01:18:54,023
What are you moaning about...

1092
01:18:55,239 --> 01:18:56,341
Papa !

1093
01:19:00,516 --> 01:19:03,146
Where is Maman ?
Your mother is with her sister,

1094
01:19:03,171 --> 01:19:04,771
And your brothers, in Savoy.

1095
01:19:04,796 --> 01:19:06,629
I stayed to find you.

1096
01:19:10,322 --> 01:19:11,905
What is that ?

1097
01:19:19,388 --> 01:19:22,786
Better a slap that hurts,
rather than never see you again.

1098
01:20:18,721 --> 01:20:21,679
Papa promised us we
would meet in Paris

1099
01:20:21,861 --> 01:20:23,536
Once the war was over.

1100
01:20:23,930 --> 01:20:27,560
But, for now, it was too
dangerous to stay together.

1101
01:21:12,628 --> 01:21:13,503
Maurice?

1102
01:21:14,411 --> 01:21:16,494
Jo. Jo, wake up.

1103
01:21:18,223 --> 01:21:19,931
Your Maman's on the phone.

1104
01:21:28,872 --> 01:21:30,580
Hi Maman ?
It's me.

1105
01:21:30,724 --> 01:21:32,432
"My darling, are you okay?"

1106
01:21:32,938 --> 01:21:34,896
You have to leave right away.

1107
01:21:35,680 --> 01:21:37,846
Your father has the
same illness you did.

1108
01:21:38,790 --> 01:21:40,396
Meningitis ?

1109
01:21:41,665 --> 01:21:42,790
Worse than that.

1110
01:21:49,998 --> 01:21:50,873
Hello?

1111
01:21:51,707 --> 01:21:54,685
I understood that she was
talking about Papa's arrest,

1112
01:21:55,665 --> 01:21:57,498
But I no longer had tears.

1113
01:21:58,138 --> 01:22:00,138
They were replaced with anger.

1114
01:22:03,199 --> 01:22:05,763
Again, we had to flee.

1115
01:22:14,248 --> 01:22:17,039
I can carry you, if you want.
Rather die.

1116
01:22:17,207 --> 01:22:20,040
I'm the big brother.
I'm the one who carries.

1117
01:22:45,540 --> 01:22:48,208
We were in touch
with the others lost.

1118
01:22:48,560 --> 01:22:50,143
But that wasn't a big deal.

1119
01:22:50,391 --> 01:22:52,849
Because if Maurice and I
had already arrived there,

1120
01:22:53,039 --> 01:22:55,080
then Papa sure would be.

1121
01:22:55,373 --> 01:22:58,248
Everything was going to be fine.
You had to believe in that.

1122
01:23:12,149 --> 01:23:15,693
While waiting for the end of the war,
Maurice and I had a job.

1123
01:23:16,021 --> 01:23:18,146
Just like Maman told us to do.

1124
01:23:18,696 --> 01:23:19,987
Any job.

1125
01:23:26,610 --> 01:23:29,552
Maurice worked in the
largest restaurant nearby...

1126
01:23:29,748 --> 01:23:34,005
and I was a delivery person for
the bookseller, Ambroise Mancelier.

1127
01:23:37,348 --> 01:23:39,181
You see, Joseph,

1128
01:23:39,813 --> 01:23:42,560
you won't learn anything
at a public school,

1129
01:23:43,087 --> 01:23:46,365
because public school
has become like a girl...

1130
01:23:47,207 --> 01:23:50,200
What characterizes the great minds,
is to have an ideal.

1131
01:23:50,582 --> 01:23:52,185
And there aren't 36 things to do.

1132
01:23:52,248 --> 01:23:54,789
No, there is only one thing to do for Europe.

1133
01:23:55,310 --> 01:23:58,435
And they are three great minds,
my dear Joseph, that Europe has made:

1134
01:23:58,795 --> 01:23:59,961
Louis XIV,

1135
01:24:00,021 --> 01:24:02,794
Napoleon Bonaparte
and Philippe Pétain.

1136
01:24:03,040 --> 01:24:05,794
"I keep my promises,
even those of others."

1137
01:24:06,638 --> 01:24:08,185
Oh, that's beautiful...

1138
01:24:08,457 --> 01:24:10,747
Congratulations, my little Joseph.

1139
01:24:13,770 --> 01:24:14,997
My son.

1140
01:24:15,332 --> 01:24:17,036
Here. Bravo.

1141
01:24:17,332 --> 01:24:18,165
Look.

1142
01:24:18,263 --> 01:24:20,833
You do good work every now
and then, in the Militia.

1143
01:24:21,388 --> 01:24:24,177
MILITIA EXPORTS 20,000 JEWS
It's just the beginning.

1144
01:24:24,582 --> 01:24:26,263
France for the French, Papa.

1145
01:24:32,138 --> 01:24:33,755
Wait a second boy...

1146
01:24:34,060 --> 01:24:37,293
You sleep under my roof and have been
working with me, for almost six months.

1147
01:24:37,630 --> 01:24:39,464
So you're part of the family, right?

1148
01:24:40,005 --> 01:24:41,082
Yes sir.

1149
01:24:41,248 --> 01:24:43,099
Your parents must miss you,

1150
01:24:43,124 --> 01:24:44,874
being so far away from you, in Algeria.

1151
01:24:45,560 --> 01:24:46,685
Yes, a lot.

1152
01:24:47,332 --> 01:24:50,888
As of today, you will eat with us...

1153
01:24:51,839 --> 01:24:56,419
but from Sunday you will also share
in something that is very dear to us...

1154
01:24:56,540 --> 01:24:58,081
the Holy Mass.

1155
01:25:03,457 --> 01:25:06,411
I understand that you are not
very devoted to the mass.

1156
01:25:06,747 --> 01:25:09,552
It is time you did as our Christian faith teaches.

1157
01:25:10,082 --> 01:25:10,915
Yes.

1158
01:25:10,982 --> 01:25:12,630
Thank you, Mr. Mancelier.

1159
01:25:18,790 --> 01:25:19,786
Newspaper!

1160
01:25:19,864 --> 01:25:22,606
'La Gerbe', 'La Proche',
'Je Suis Partout'!

1161
01:25:24,341 --> 01:25:27,757
'La Gerbe', 'Le Petit Dauphinois',
'Je Suis Partout', the newspaper!

1162
01:25:27,797 --> 01:25:29,435
Who wants the newspaper?

1163
01:25:29,477 --> 01:25:30,834
Let's see, little one.

1164
01:25:30,859 --> 01:25:32,122
Oh no, thank you.

1165
01:25:36,065 --> 01:25:37,440
'La Gerbe', 'Le Dauphinois'!

1166
01:25:37,649 --> 01:25:38,649
'Je Suis Partout'!

1167
01:25:38,774 --> 01:25:40,185
La Gerbe. The newspaper ?

1168
01:25:40,315 --> 01:25:42,981
The Dauphinois!  La Gerbe!
I'm everywhere!

1169
01:25:43,122 --> 01:25:44,607
Good morning, Ms. Loca.

1170
01:25:44,763 --> 01:25:46,940
Oh! Sorry.
My brakes are not working.

1171
01:25:47,107 --> 01:25:48,021
I take the  Gerbe.

1172
01:25:48,046 --> 01:25:49,247
La Gerbe ?
Yes.

1173
01:25:49,365 --> 01:25:51,524
Thank you. Have a good day.

1174
01:25:51,841 --> 01:25:54,083
The Vichy newspaper, Mr. Julien?

1175
01:25:54,108 --> 01:25:56,524
La Gerbe ?  I'm everywhere ?

1176
01:25:57,763 --> 01:25:59,221
Over my dead body.

1177
01:26:00,818 --> 01:26:04,740
Here, keep your newspaper. Is he
still always so stupid, that Mancelier?

1178
01:26:04,765 --> 01:26:05,765
Always.

1179
01:26:18,760 --> 01:26:20,801
Hello. Here, the newspapers.

1180
01:26:21,326 --> 01:26:22,159
Hey, Jo!

1181
01:26:24,065 --> 01:26:24,981
Shh.

1182
01:26:26,677 --> 01:26:28,927
The penguin flaps its wings.

1183
01:26:29,823 --> 01:26:30,656
The Penguin

1184
01:26:30,935 --> 01:26:33,226
- What is this?
- The penguin flaps its wings.

1185
01:26:33,251 --> 01:26:35,615
Encoded messages for the Resistance.

1186
01:26:36,010 --> 01:26:38,176
The ghost doesn't talk.

1187
01:26:38,786 --> 01:26:41,244
Good. I'm going because
Mancelier will call me.

1188
01:26:45,041 --> 01:26:47,833
By the way, how is she,
the girl of the collaborators?

1189
01:26:48,549 --> 01:26:50,318
Why do you want to know that ?

1190
01:26:50,620 --> 01:26:53,122
Still in love with
your little Francoise?

1191
01:26:53,582 --> 01:26:54,724
What does that mean?

1192
01:26:54,874 --> 01:26:56,540
5 months that you look at her?

1193
01:26:57,349 --> 01:26:59,154
Has she talked with you or not?

1194
01:26:59,973 --> 01:27:01,806
I'm making progress...

1195
01:27:10,149 --> 01:27:13,482
And you, your entrance into the Resistance,
are you making any progress?

1196
01:27:14,430 --> 01:27:15,721
Don't start on that.

1197
01:27:15,746 --> 01:27:17,829
Do they send you coded messages?

1198
01:27:19,220 --> 01:27:20,053
Yes

1199
01:27:22,540 --> 01:27:25,206
"Françoise has hair on her legs.
I repeat: Françoise has..."

1200
01:27:25,232 --> 01:27:26,716
You're really miserable!

1201
01:27:26,816 --> 01:27:27,816
The Militia!

1202
01:27:31,786 --> 01:27:33,831
Maurice, hide everything.

1203
01:27:33,970 --> 01:27:35,646
You send the message.

1204
01:27:41,334 --> 01:27:42,167
Hold on.

1205
01:27:42,540 --> 01:27:43,831
Lets' go.

1206
01:27:43,857 --> 01:27:44,957
Its good.

1207
01:27:45,251 --> 01:27:48,075
Jo, give that to sir Jean
in the factory. Come on!

1208
01:27:48,249 --> 01:27:50,021
Nobody moves.
You stay here.

1209
01:27:50,060 --> 01:27:51,125
Maureler, hurry.
- We are here.

1210
01:27:51,149 --> 01:27:52,149
I'll take the floor.

1211
01:27:52,249 --> 01:27:53,404
Search it all.

1212
01:27:53,429 --> 01:27:54,387
Show me.

1213
01:27:54,983 --> 01:27:57,685
What have you got in here?
What are you hiding?

1214
01:28:02,693 --> 01:28:04,896
Remove your hand.
What's this ?

1215
01:28:08,325 --> 01:28:09,613
Empty your pockets.

1216
01:28:09,953 --> 01:28:11,244
- Me ?
- Yes, yes, you.

1217
01:28:11,269 --> 01:28:14,443
I have the impression that you are
a rat and are hiding something.

1218
01:28:19,921 --> 01:28:21,865
Go away. Here's your marble.

1219
01:28:21,935 --> 01:28:24,268
Don't come here anymore.
Understood?

1220
01:28:31,665 --> 01:28:32,927
So what?

1221
01:28:33,036 --> 01:28:34,802
What are you doing here?

1222
01:28:35,019 --> 01:28:37,352
With what right do you
come inside people's homes?

1223
01:28:57,930 --> 01:28:58,763
Who is he?

1224
01:28:59,499 --> 01:29:02,499
The newspaper delivery boy.
He wants to talk to Mr. Jean.

1225
01:29:04,298 --> 01:29:06,020
What do you want to say to him?

1226
01:29:06,214 --> 01:29:09,630
Paul, at the Hotel du Commerce,
gave me something for him.

1227
01:29:10,348 --> 01:29:12,051
What does Paul look like?

1228
01:29:12,290 --> 01:29:16,161
Pretty big, round glasses,
hair brushed to the side.

1229
01:29:20,014 --> 01:29:21,305
Give me the message.

1230
01:29:21,415 --> 01:29:22,965
I have to give it to Mr. Jean.

1231
01:29:22,990 --> 01:29:25,031
I am Mr. Jean.
Go.

1232
01:29:26,387 --> 01:29:27,590
Come on, hand it over.

1233
01:29:27,915 --> 01:29:29,331
It's him, give it to him.

1234
01:29:31,319 --> 01:29:32,348
Take over.

1235
01:29:32,373 --> 01:29:33,411
Follow me.

1236
01:29:35,790 --> 01:29:36,918
Close the door.

1237
01:29:40,992 --> 01:29:42,715
There is water in the gas.

1238
01:29:42,740 --> 01:29:44,770
"The Chamois of the Alps jumps."

1239
01:29:45,352 --> 01:29:49,614
We've been waiting for that for a while.
Congratulations, little one. Well done.

1240
01:29:50,053 --> 01:29:52,457
Maryse will tell you if
we ever need you again.

1241
01:29:53,457 --> 01:29:54,290
Come on.

1242
01:29:58,536 --> 01:30:00,665
Attention, Francoise, it's hot.

1243
01:30:00,832 --> 01:30:01,731
Yes!

1244
01:30:03,090 --> 01:30:04,340
Yes !

1245
01:30:05,286 --> 01:30:07,415
Hello. I'm sorry for the delay.

1246
01:30:07,488 --> 01:30:09,332
You lost yourself in the attic?

1247
01:30:12,624 --> 01:30:15,457
- Shut the door, please.
- Yes, excuse me.

1248
01:30:18,832 --> 01:30:19,998
What are you doing here?

1249
01:30:20,036 --> 01:30:21,957
Well, Mr. Mancelier...

1250
01:30:21,982 --> 01:30:24,286
- You get out.
- Leave him alone.

1251
01:30:24,874 --> 01:30:27,301
It was Papa who invited him.

1252
01:30:30,165 --> 01:30:31,831
And here is the beast!

1253
01:30:32,082 --> 01:30:33,895
- There you go.
- Joseph, at the table.

1254
01:30:34,790 --> 01:30:36,973
Sit yourself next to Raoul, over there.

1255
01:30:37,276 --> 01:30:40,301
I raise my glass... to all mothers

1256
01:30:40,707 --> 01:30:44,286
And to all the women who
will bare children in their bellies,

1257
01:30:44,411 --> 01:30:45,723
for the France of tomorrow.

1258
01:30:45,802 --> 01:30:47,317
Happy birthday, ladies.

1259
01:30:47,789 --> 01:30:49,348
Thank you.
Thank you.

1260
01:30:49,945 --> 01:30:54,411
"You are the inspiration of
our Christian civilization."

1261
01:30:54,449 --> 01:30:57,239
- Who said that?
- Marshal Petain, papa.

1262
01:30:57,569 --> 01:30:58,707
Exactly.

1263
01:30:58,878 --> 01:31:00,684
How can we treat "sold" men

1264
01:31:00,797 --> 01:31:02,903
who glorified Mother's Day?

1265
01:31:03,665 --> 01:31:05,915
My God, help the Marshal to resist.

1266
01:31:06,046 --> 01:31:07,450
And Adolf Hitler.

1267
01:31:07,586 --> 01:31:11,575
If one had allied himself to him in 1936,
with Franco and Mussolini,

1268
01:31:12,403 --> 01:31:14,457
England would not have fired

1269
01:31:14,566 --> 01:31:16,520
and Europe was ours.
Anyway.

1270
01:31:16,684 --> 01:31:18,153
And we did not?

1271
01:31:18,178 --> 01:31:20,739
Because our government had become rotten

1272
01:31:20,764 --> 01:31:22,551
by Jewish vermin.

1273
01:31:22,679 --> 01:31:25,557
Hitler did a good job.

1274
01:31:25,582 --> 01:31:28,684
There's no other way.
Be up to the challenge.

1275
01:31:28,709 --> 01:31:31,731
In any case, we're going to
exterminate them, these rats.

1276
01:31:32,382 --> 01:31:35,543
They may hide in their holes,
they will all go through it.

1277
01:31:37,042 --> 01:31:39,278
 In the meantime, help us to drink.

1278
01:31:40,912 --> 01:31:44,536
My brother, he's a jerk.
He is anti-everything.

1279
01:31:45,000 --> 01:31:48,265
Anti-republican, anti-communist,
anti-capitalist...

1280
01:31:48,290 --> 01:31:49,456
Antisemitic.

1281
01:31:50,047 --> 01:31:52,114
That too, yes, more than anything else.

1282
01:31:52,985 --> 01:31:55,401
He thinks like your father.
Well yeah.

1283
01:31:55,606 --> 01:31:57,661
They're the same, those two.

1284
01:31:57,817 --> 01:32:00,082
I, too, think like my father.

1285
01:32:00,211 --> 01:32:03,002
Who is your father?
You never talk about him.

1286
01:32:03,707 --> 01:32:05,082
Well, that's my father.

1287
01:32:10,270 --> 01:32:12,512
You are mysterious,
you and your brothers.

1288
01:32:12,889 --> 01:32:15,989
True, we do wonder what you hide.

1289
01:32:16,493 --> 01:32:17,784
That, "we"

1290
01:32:18,190 --> 01:32:19,773
Me and my girlfriends.

1291
01:32:34,155 --> 01:32:35,559
Francoise. Listen.

1292
01:32:35,931 --> 01:32:37,722
I have to tell you something.

1293
01:32:38,039 --> 01:32:41,403
I don't have the right to say it,
but I can tell it to you.

1294
01:32:42,042 --> 01:32:43,833
Because I trust you.

1295
01:32:44,499 --> 01:32:46,614
Are you sure you're okay?
Yes.

1296
01:32:49,631 --> 01:32:51,676
Well, go ahead. I'm listening to you.

1297
01:32:52,374 --> 01:32:53,309
I am...

1298
01:32:54,499 --> 01:32:55,551
I am...

1299
01:33:00,363 --> 01:33:03,154
Do not worry, I get it.

1300
01:33:05,578 --> 01:33:06,536
Come on.

1301
01:33:08,985 --> 01:33:10,818
Come quickly. Quick.

1302
01:33:16,545 --> 01:33:18,700
Hurry up.
Go up the stairs.

1303
01:33:25,637 --> 01:33:26,551
Hey, you.

1304
01:33:27,832 --> 01:33:28,707
The.

1305
01:33:29,455 --> 01:33:31,137
It's my brother.

1306
01:33:37,477 --> 01:33:38,582
Aim.

1307
01:33:40,469 --> 01:33:41,614
Fire!

1308
01:33:48,749 --> 01:33:49,653
Freedom,

1309
01:33:49,715 --> 01:33:51,879
Equality, Fra...

1310
01:33:56,874 --> 01:33:58,114
Take them away.

1311
01:34:14,363 --> 01:34:16,934
Fortunately they did not take you,
the Resistance.

1312
01:34:18,915 --> 01:34:21,067
You might be dead now.

1313
01:34:21,332 --> 01:34:25,051
Imagine having to tell our parents?
And Henry and Albert?

1314
01:34:29,165 --> 01:34:32,498
It's the English.
No, it's the Americans.

1315
01:34:33,790 --> 01:34:36,956
You know what that means?
We'll see them soon.

1316
01:34:49,540 --> 01:34:50,915
Death to the Militia!

1317
01:34:51,030 --> 01:34:54,020
You will pay for all
those who have died.

1318
01:34:54,089 --> 01:34:55,965
Death to the collaborators!

1319
01:35:11,709 --> 01:35:13,793
Band of bastards!

1320
01:35:14,077 --> 01:35:17,368
You want to give France
back to England? Cretin!

1321
01:35:19,837 --> 01:35:23,378
The English are the historic enemy.
Not the Germans.

1322
01:35:23,600 --> 01:35:25,152
Species of imbeciles!

1323
01:35:33,085 --> 01:35:34,606
What are we going to do ?

1324
01:35:34,644 --> 01:35:37,137
It's Waterloo, we lost.

1325
01:35:37,162 --> 01:35:39,498
Be careful Françoise,
that glass will cut you.

1326
01:35:40,285 --> 01:35:42,973
The little one, Ambroise,
must be protected.

1327
01:35:43,749 --> 01:35:45,317
You must take Françoise
to my sister's house.

1328
01:35:45,342 --> 01:35:48,629
Your daughter, your mother, your sister!
I do not care !

1329
01:36:06,702 --> 01:36:08,957
I know what it's like
to leave, you know.

1330
01:36:11,378 --> 01:36:13,965
Everyone in my family had
to leave at one time.

1331
01:36:16,488 --> 01:36:20,207
My father said, "Do not look
behind you when you walk.

1332
01:36:21,797 --> 01:36:24,047
"Otherwise we break our mouths."

1333
01:36:29,800 --> 01:36:32,161
I'm sure you're like your father.

1334
01:36:49,770 --> 01:36:50,998
It's not true !

1335
01:36:55,933 --> 01:36:58,599
Joseph! Joseph!

1336
01:36:58,945 --> 01:37:00,645
What's happening now?

1337
01:37:04,944 --> 01:37:06,194
Misery...

1338
01:37:07,459 --> 01:37:09,075
Paris is liberated!

1339
01:37:09,374 --> 01:37:10,856
Paris is liberated!

1340
01:37:10,915 --> 01:37:13,123
Attention. Paris is liberated!

1341
01:37:13,465 --> 01:37:14,262
Attention.

1342
01:37:14,287 --> 01:37:15,748
Paris is liberated!

1343
01:37:15,999 --> 01:37:17,040
Attention

1344
01:37:17,207 --> 01:37:18,832
Paris is liberated!

1345
01:37:19,360 --> 01:37:22,026
Read the newspaper! Paris is liberated!

1346
01:37:22,749 --> 01:37:25,067
The newspaper! Paris is liberated!

1347
01:37:27,832 --> 01:37:30,246
Paris is liberated! They left!

1348
01:37:30,271 --> 01:37:33,271
They're gone, Jojo.
They left.

1349
01:37:33,563 --> 01:37:35,729
They're gone, it's over.

1350
01:37:51,499 --> 01:37:55,114
Look, they're going to Paris.
Go get your brother.

1351
01:37:59,582 --> 01:38:01,387
My dear fellow-citizens,

1352
01:38:01,412 --> 01:38:03,543
today is a big day.

1353
01:38:04,487 --> 01:38:07,320
We are finally free!

1354
01:38:45,514 --> 01:38:48,222
Sleeping with the Germans!
Treacherous!

1355
01:38:51,040 --> 01:38:51,873
Jo!

1356
01:38:52,551 --> 01:38:53,676
Maurice!

1357
01:38:55,648 --> 01:38:56,895
Do you believe it?

1358
01:38:56,920 --> 01:38:59,044
No. It's finally over.

1359
01:38:59,430 --> 01:39:01,388
Come. Cars are going back to Paris.

1360
01:39:02,653 --> 01:39:04,661
- What?
- There's room for us.

1361
01:39:04,780 --> 01:39:07,332
Go get your things.
We're going back.

1362
01:39:16,871 --> 01:39:18,496
No, I cannot.

1363
01:39:20,988 --> 01:39:23,571
Go yourself.
I'll meet you later.

1364
01:39:24,153 --> 01:39:25,317
You're sure?

1365
01:39:25,642 --> 01:39:26,989
What would you do?

1366
01:39:28,152 --> 01:39:29,793
We're free, are we not?

1367
01:39:31,434 --> 01:39:32,600
We're free, yes.

1368
01:39:33,737 --> 01:39:36,668
Tell our parents I'm
coming and I love them.

1369
01:39:41,776 --> 01:39:43,839
Are you going to cope, all by yourself?

1370
01:39:44,098 --> 01:39:45,098
And you?

1371
01:39:45,559 --> 01:39:47,392
You're gonna get away without me?

1372
01:39:48,637 --> 01:39:50,739
Come on, go find her.

1373
01:40:00,988 --> 01:40:02,196
Francoise!

1374
01:40:05,831 --> 01:40:07,184
Francoise!

1375
01:40:09,805 --> 01:40:12,364
No. Stop! Stop!

1376
01:40:13,068 --> 01:40:15,192
Stop! Stop!

1377
01:40:19,821 --> 01:40:23,145
Stop! He hid a Jew!

1378
01:40:23,292 --> 01:40:24,738
What are you saying ?

1379
01:40:24,820 --> 01:40:26,028
Is that true Jo ?

1380
01:40:26,364 --> 01:40:27,364
It's true.

1381
01:40:28,135 --> 01:40:31,301
That bastard would never hide a Jew.

1382
01:40:31,566 --> 01:40:32,942
I swear to you.

1383
01:40:33,433 --> 01:40:34,668
And who then?

1384
01:40:35,703 --> 01:40:36,619
Me.

1385
01:40:40,253 --> 01:40:41,503
I am Jewish.

1386
01:40:44,809 --> 01:40:45,934
I am Jewish!

1387
01:40:46,348 --> 01:40:49,387
I am Jewish! I am Jewish!

1388
01:40:49,933 --> 01:40:51,621
I am Jewish!

1389
01:40:54,021 --> 01:40:55,098
Did he know?"

1390
01:40:55,531 --> 01:40:57,161
Of course he knew.

1391
01:40:58,446 --> 01:41:01,004
Nevertheless, he is a collaborator.

1392
01:41:08,082 --> 01:41:10,404
He did it so he would
not be suspected.

1393
01:41:10,464 --> 01:41:11,755
We're embarking.

1394
01:41:12,328 --> 01:41:14,778
Go to the hole,
and wait for the judge.

1395
01:41:20,688 --> 01:41:23,864
And Marcelle, we'll
shave her head anyway.

1396
01:41:29,404 --> 01:41:30,404
Thank you.

1397
01:41:32,854 --> 01:41:35,187
Where is she, Francoise?

1398
01:42:00,738 --> 01:42:02,325
Francoise, wait!

1399
01:42:03,113 --> 01:42:04,293
Francoise!

1400
01:42:05,029 --> 01:42:06,231
Francoise!

1401
01:42:08,488 --> 01:42:10,279
Francoise, wait!

1402
01:43:54,810 --> 01:43:55,996
Papa?

1403
01:43:57,571 --> 01:43:58,786
Papa!

1404
01:44:02,602 --> 01:44:03,685
Papa!

1405
01:44:24,154 --> 01:44:25,434
Maman!

1406
01:44:25,855 --> 01:44:27,504
Maman, Jojo is back!

1407
01:44:27,529 --> 01:44:28,852
Maman, it's me!

1408
01:44:29,029 --> 01:44:30,450
Jojo!

1409
01:44:31,029 --> 01:44:33,028
Maurice, your brother is here!

1410
01:46:12,028 --> 01:46:12,986
Papa.

1411
01:46:30,113 --> 01:46:32,613
Papa, do you remember?

1412
01:46:33,957 --> 01:46:36,778
You told me that when
a good man dies,

1413
01:46:37,193 --> 01:46:41,309
a star in the sky lights up,
and one had to keep hope.

1414
01:46:42,279 --> 01:46:43,637
Well, that's true.

1415
01:46:44,029 --> 01:46:47,529
You're here, papa, and
you'll always be.

1416
01:46:50,668 --> 01:46:55,676
In April 1944, Anna, Albert and Henri were arrested
in their flight, then interned in the Drancy camp.

1417
01:46:55,770 --> 01:46:59,043
Due to a lack of trains,
they narrowly escaped deportation.

1418
01:46:59,106 --> 01:47:02,137
The Red Cross released them shortly before
the Americans arrived in August 1944.

1419
01:47:02,178 --> 01:47:05,066
The family was thus able to return to Paris.

1420
01:47:06,557 --> 01:47:11,080
Roman, brought by convoy no. 62 to Auschwitz
in November 1943, never returned.

1421
01:47:21,293 --> 01:47:28,188
In 1945, Joseph and Maurice took over their father's hairdressing salon
with their brothers, thus perpetuating the family tradition.

1422
01:47:28,226 --> 01:47:33,196
They still live in Paris, surrounded by their children and grandchildren.

1423
01:52:07,616 --> 01:52:10,741
Subtitles: Eclair Media
